    value: The practice of inscriptions in tombs (epitaphs) was central to Confucian commemoration, preserving the virtues of the deceased for posterity.
  - key: ''
    value: The Master's decision to resign and return to care for his aging mother represents the Confucian hierarchy of obligations, where filial piety supersedes official duty.
